-- Mexico Stocks: Cemex, Grupo Modelo, Homex, Ica Are Active
-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 2012-03-12T17:56:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-12/mexico-stocks-cemex-grupo-modelo-homex-ica-are-active.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Mexico  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 11:21 a.m. local time.  The IPC index fell 0.4 percent to 37,556.27.  Construction-related companies led Mexican stocks lower
after  China  posted the biggest trade deficit last month in at
least 22 years and the weakest January-February factory-
production gain since 2009.  Cemex SAB (CEMEXCPO), the largest cement maker in the
Americas, fell 1.9 percent to 9.93 pesos.  Desarrolladora Homex
SAB (HOMEX*)  , Mexico’s largest homebuilder, fell 1.4 percent
to 39.30 pesos.  Empresas Ica SAB (ICA*)  , the country’s
biggest construction company, slipped 1.9 percent to 22.68
pesos.  Defensive beverage companies were among the country’s
biggest gainers.  Grupo Modelo SAB (GMODELOC MM), Mexico’s largest beer
maker, rose 2.1 percent to 88.45 pesos.  Coca-Cola Femsa (KOF)  SAB, Latin America’s largest Coca-Cola bottler, rose 1.1
percent to 129.61 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jonathan J. Levin in Mexico City at 
 jlevin20@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
